  [1] Or if you have millions of dollars in   FDIC-insurance-arbitrage prod=
ucts spread out   among many banks.


  [2] There are non-governmental versions of this: If your bank is a big ba=
nk, then you might think something like =E2=80=9CI am sure the fact that JP=
Morgan has zillions of dollars of deposits and Jamie Dimon is treated as an=
 oracle means that someone has checked to make sure they run a good busines=
s=E2=80=9D; you can sort of rely on the wisdom of the market to vouch for y=
our big famous bank. But with smaller regional banks this argument seems le=
ss compelling, and you are relying more on =E2=80=9Cwell the US banking sys=
tem is generally well run so my particular bank is probably fine.=E2=80=9D


  [3] We have talked about this question =E2=80=94 =E2=80=9Care regional ba=
nks good=E2=80=9D or whatever =E2=80=94 before;   I have suggested that reg=
ional banks seem good at certain kinds of lending but kind of bad at being =
funded by flighty deposits.=20


  [4] We have talked in the past about more nuanced versions of this argume=
nt. If you are an ESG investor, you might think of your role not as =E2=80=
=9Cget companies to drill less oil to mitigate climate change,=E2=80=9D and=
 more =E2=80=9Cget companies to drill less oil to mitigate the *financial r=
isks to themselves* of climate change=E2=80=9D: As the world warms,   the a=
rgument goes, people will use less reasons for consumer-preference or regul=
atory reasons, so an oil company that goes all in on oil exploration will g=
o broke, and it should either hedge by investing in wind farms or just plan=
 for decline by doing buybacks. Also   we have discussed Samuel Hartzmark a=
nd Kelly Shue=E2=80=99s argument that ESG investing has the effect of raisi=
ng the cost of capital of =E2=80=9Cdirty=E2=80=9D firms, which causes them =
to engage in more short-term thinking; stock buybacks are often thought of =
as a classic form of managerial short-termism, where managers have no good =
long-term plans so just hand their earnings back to shareholders.=20


  [5] I will say that my anecdotal experience is that, after Musk=E2=80=99s=
 takeover, I saw a noticeable *increase* in crypto spam bots, though to be =
fair that might have been because I was writing too much about crypto. But =
in recent weeks it has gotten much better, so I am inclined to think he *ha=
s* done something to address the problem.


