<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A core concept in the crypto financial system =
is the box. This is not an official term or anything, but it=E2=80=99s how =
I think of it; the term <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/31793244.260412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZnR4LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1zaGVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MTQy=
M19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV9=
0ZXJtPTIzMDYxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB36=
0d4783" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">  comes from</a> something that Sam Bankman-Fried said to m=
e on a podcast. Here=E2=80=99s how it works:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You start some project or business or=
 blockchain or whatever.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You issue=
 a token for the project. The token may or may not have some sort of claim =
on the cash flows of the project, or some governance rights over it, but in=
 any case it is the token=C2=A0<em>of=C2=A0</em>the project, and its price =
will fluctuate based on people=E2=80=99s perception of the project, their e=
xpectations for its future, its actual success, etc. The price of the token=
 will reflect the value of the project in some loose way.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You give yourself a lot of the token.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You multiply the trading price of the token (w=
hich reflects the market value of the project) times the number of tokens t=
hat you have (which is probably large, since you made up the token and can =
give yourself as much as you want), and you get a large dollar number.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You probably cannot=C2=A0<em>sell </em=
>your tokens for that large dollar number: If you dumped all your tokens at=
 once, confidence in the project would fall, supply would swamp demand, the=
 price of the token would collapse and you probably wouldn=E2=80=99t get ve=
ry much money for your stash.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But =
you can turn the tokens into money in other ways. You can borrow against th=
em; if you say =E2=80=9Chey I have $10=C2=A0billion of tokens=E2=80=9D some=
 crypto lender might give you a $5 billion secured loan.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">More broadly, you can say =E2=80=9CI am a billiona=
ire, what with my $10 billion of tokens,=E2=80=9D and people will tend to t=
rust you more and give you more economic opportunities because you=E2=80=99=
re a billionaire. If you put in a bid to buy a mansion or a sports team or =
whatever, people will take you seriously because you have $10 billion (of t=
okens). If your bid is successful, a bank will probably lend you the money =
to buy the mansion or sports team. The loan will not necessarily be=C2=A0<e=
m>secured by=C2=A0</em>your $10 billion pile of tokens, but the bank=E2=80=
=99s credit decision will probably be like =E2=80=9Cthis person has $10 bil=
lion, she=E2=80=99s good for this loan.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">And people will be more willing to deal with=C2=A0<em>=
your project </em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0or business or blockchain or whatever, the=
 thing that started all of this =E2=80=94=C2=A0because there=E2=80=99s $10 =
billion behind it. =E2=80=9CI will trade on this crypto exchange without wo=
rrying about it getting hacked, because if it gets hacked surely it will ma=
ke up my losses, because it has $10 billion.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not something that crypto invented, or=
 that is limited to crypto.=C2=A0Lots of people found regular companies, is=
sue stock of those companies, keep a lot of stock for themselves, and eithe=
r explicitly borrow against that stock (margin loans, etc.) or at least poi=
nt to their huge pile of stock as proof that they are rich and leverage tha=
t wealth to buy other things. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/31793244.260412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGl=
jbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMTUvaWNhaG4taGFzLWZhY2VkLW1hbnktcHJvYmVzLWJ1dC1oaW5kZW5idX=
JnLWNsYWltcy1zdGFuZC1hcGFydD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjE0MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVka=
XVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA2MTQmdXRtX2NhbXBh=
aWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8e79a0bd" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">
Carl Icahn</a> has margin loans against his Icahn Enterprises stock. Elon M=
usk has margin loans against his Tesla Inc. stock; also, though, he was cle=
arly able to get financing to buy Twitter Inc. (<em>not=C2=A0</em>secured b=
y his Tesla stock) because banks were like =E2=80=9Cyeah, this guy=E2=80=99=
s rich, we=E2=80=99ll lend him money even if we think that the Twitter deal=
 is kind of a dog.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nor is any of this really=C2=A0<em>wrong</em>;=
 I am not necessarily describing a fraud or a mistake or anything. It just =
sort of depends on what the project is? The problem is that a lot of stuff =
in crypto is a=C2=A0<em>pure=C2=A0</em>confidence business: Tesla makes car=
s, and if people lost confidence in its stock there would still be cars, bu=
t many crypto projects just make crypto trades, and if people lost confiden=
ce in their crypto trades there=E2=80=99d be nothing left. It is a very wro=
ng-way risk; the pile of money safeguarding your business evaporates in exa=
ctly the circumstances that your business is in trouble.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other problem is that at least some people=
 in crypto were=C2=A0<em>very=C2=A0</em>self-aware of this dynamic. It is o=
ne thing to start a car company, issue stock to finance factories, keep sto=
ck for yourself as the founder, get rich on paper, and then borrow against =
your vast stock wealth to finance a rocket company or whatever =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0each decision there is plausibly about building a real business. It is a=
nother thing to think =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99m gonna issue some tokens beca=
use if I can get people to buy them I can borrow a lot of money and walk aw=
ay from the mess.=E2=80=9D There is adverse selection there. I am not sayin=
g everyone in crypto thought that. I am just saying that Sam Bankman-Fried=
=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31793244.260=
412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjUvc2F=
tLWJhbmttYW4tZnJpZWQtZGVzY3JpYmVkLXlpZWxkLWZhcm1pbmctYW5kLWxlZnQtbWF0dC1sZX=
ZpbmUtc3R1bm5lZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjE0MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJ=
nV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA2MTQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5=
c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2f3c4e95" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
