ce, its rainy day fund has fallen in value by 11%.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fund was valued at nearly $950 million at =
the start of the month, according to blockchain addresses that Binance says=
 hold the assets. After the Securities and Exchange Commission sued Binance=
 last week, it fell to some $840 million.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fund=E2=80=94dubbed the secure asset fund =
for users, or SAFU for short=E2=80=94is meant to cover losses from hacks or=
 other compromises of Binance=E2=80=99s systems. Changpeng Zhao, Binance=E2=
=80=99s founder, has also mentioned it in times of stress to give comfort t=
o users, including when rival FTX collapsed. It holds a combination of bitc=
oin, dollar-pegged cryptocurrencies and a coin created by Binance, BNB.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That token, BNB, plays an outsize role in SAFU=
=E2=80=94accounting for roughly half the dollar value.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BNB has tumbled more than 20% after the SEC su=
it alleged that Binance=E2=80=99s overseas company operated an illegal trad=
ing platform in the U.S. and misused customers=E2=80=99 funds.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
